                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#129vb">f. 129vb</locus>: Donation note.<quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="129vb">129vb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፈ፡ ፍትሐት፡ ዘወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘአቡሃ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ወእማ፡ ላህየ፡ ድንግል፡ ወብእሲሃ፡ ሀብተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዝውእቱ፡ ግራ፡ አዝማች፡ ወሰን፡ ወውሉዳ፡ ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ትንሣኤ። ዘአጽሐፈቶ፡ በንዋያ፡ ወወሀበቶ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ማርያም፡ ታብር፡ እንተ፡ ትሰመይ፡ ማይ፡ ራዛ። …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that Walatta Mikāʾel donated the book to the church of Māryām Tabǝr (?) which is called May Raza. It also mentions her parents Walda Māryām and Lahǝyä Dǝngǝl, her husband gǝra ʾazmač Habta Śǝllāse and her children. The head of the monastery Ḫayla ʾIyasus is mentioned as the scribe.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="2r">2r</locus>: Crude drawing of a cross (?).&#xD;
- The title of the book is crudely written on <locus target="2r">2r</locus>.&#xD;
- The names of the donors are written on <locus target="130vb">130vb</locus>.&#xD;
- A crude frame in red ink is drawn around four lines: <locus target="59va">59va</locus>.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="15ab">15ab</locus>, 44rb, 52ra, 53vb, 54ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="3rb">3rb</locus>, 4rb, 5ra, 6vb, 7vab.&#xD;
- Tamallas-sign indicating the place where the omission, written in the outer or upper margin, belongs: e.g., <locus target="9va">9va</locus>, 13ra, 15va, 27ra, 29rb.&#xD;
- Compressed script: e.g., <locus from="28vb" to="30ra">28vb-30ra</locus>, 47va-48va, 52vb-53va.&#xD;
- አም ቷቲ ሙአ አን ፋሲ (musical annotation signs?) is written in very small letters above the abbreviation ሃ፡ሃ፡ሃ፡ሃ፡: e.g., <locus target="9va">9va</locus>b, 10rab, 10vab, 12rab.</item>
                     </list>
